    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2005 Porsche 911 Carrera (997.1) features the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six, delivering linear power through a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis remains taut with original PASM dampers, providing exceptional lateral grip and communicative steering feedback. Mechanically sound, the engine benefits from a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recently serviced rear main seal (RMS). While the paint shows minor road patina consistent with spirited use, the internals are robust, featuring optimized oil cooling and a factory-spec limited-slip differential. A driver-focused example ready for the apex.",
